text = "Venus, often called \"Earth's Twin\" is the planet that makes the closest approach to us, and shares similar characteristics. However, its atmosphere is a sheer contrast to ours, its hostile surface is covered in volcanoes, pressure is 90 times that on Earth and acid clouds rain down from the sky."
